<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF14CEC4FCD5FF37DFCB3E9F" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF14CEC4FCD5FF37DE6A3DBF" blockId="153.[810,1452,230,689]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF14CEC4FCD5FF37D8F73D2E" bold="true" box="[810,932,230,256]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species in the group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF14CEC4FB2FFF36DFAF3D2E" box="[1232,1276,231,256]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tutu">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF14CEC4FB2FFF36DFAF3D2E" box="[1232,1276,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">tutu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are recognized by the small total length; embolus with three keels; serrated area on prolateral embolus small or, when large, representedbysparsesmalldenticles;patternsofcoloration on legs and palp, when present, inconspicuous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF14CEC4FCA0FE4BDFCB3E9F" blockId="153.[810,1452,230,689]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
